==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: downwind
<hw>down"wind</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <def>on the side or in the direction
away from the direction from which the wind is blowing; in the direction
toward which the wind is blowing; <as>as, good hunters stay
<ex>downwind</ex> of their prey</as>. Opposite of <ant>upwind</ant>, and
<ant>windward</ant>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> lee(prenominal), leeward.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Downy</ent>⟦br⟧
